					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-9855290#post-4367743</guid>
				<title>Headcanons</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-9855290/scp-2348#post-4367743</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 18 Sep 2019 15:40:45 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>someauthordude</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5643926</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Spoilers?</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Drop&nbsp;down&nbsp;dropdown</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Collapse&nbsp;collapsible</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>The anomaly is semantic, similarly to <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2565">Allison Eckhart</a> or <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-1539">SCP-1539</a>. Anything that passes through is redefined as “sky”. Cognitohazardous and ontokinetic elements are also involved.</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>And now for <a href="https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WildMassGuessing">Wild! Mass! Guessing!</a><sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-426977-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" >1</a></sup></p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Drop&nbsp;down&nbsp;dropdown</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Collapse&nbsp;collapsible</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>SCP-2348 is a sky deity. This is no mere Zeus/Jupiter or Ra, however. This is a <em>conceptual</em> sky deity. This thing is a physical manifestation of the <em>concept</em> of “sky”. Apparently, this thing is such a powerful manifestation that it redefines objects passing through them to “sky”. It also draws in the sky around it, explaining the sub-anomalies. For the purpose of anyone around it, it <em>is</em> the entire sky. The “hand” imagery is due to human failure of comprehension. 2348 is shaped like a manipulative body part, incomprehensible to humans and rationalized as a hand. The pointing form is due to the manipulative body part moving into a manipulation phase, from the sky taking action. This is basically a sky god as Lovecraft or maybe <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=571081&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1568839367" alt="qntm" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=571081)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" >qntm</a></span> would write it. A new addition to the “conceptual pantheon” beside <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-3125">f i f t h</a>, god of distortion, and the <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2747">anafabula</a>, god of destruction.</p> </div> </div> </div> <div class="footnotes-footer"> <div class="title">Footnotes</div> <div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-426977-1"><a href="javascript:;" >1</a>. To be read like they read <a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wheel_of_Fortune_(American_game_show)">Wheel of Fortune</a> in the intro.</div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
